comments: Poeltl (TOR) establishes himself in Knox II's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs as Knox II defends over the pick.
Duren (DET) moves alongside Siakam's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Cunningham (DET) places his forearm to Barnes' (TOR) front as they come together and marginal contact occurs prior to his step back move.
Poeltl (TOR) is already in Bogdanovic's (DET) path and is firming up as marginal contact occurs following the handoff.
Duren (DET) jumps verticality and absorbs the marginal contact during Barnes'(TOR) driving shot attempt.
Bogdanovic (DET) and Poeltl (TOR) engage in marginal arm to arm contact prior to disengaging during the loose ball.

Ivey (DET) slightly extends his arm and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr.'s (TOR) face during his drive to the basket.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Barnes (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Poeltl (TOR) initiates contact with Knox II's (DET) wrist, and the contact affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Duren (DET) jumps towards Barnes' (TOR) and initiates contact with Barnes' head while defending his shot attempt at the rim.
Knox II (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Siakam (TOR) prior to incidental arm contact occurring during the drive.
Siakam (TOR) initiates more than marginal contact to Cunningham's (DET) head/face.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Duren (DET).
Bogdanovic (DET) initiates contact with Schroder's (TOR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
After Schroder (TOR) gathers the loose ball, Cunningham (DET) moves alongside his path and marginal body contact occurs as Schroder releases his pass attempt.
Porter Jr. (TOR) commits a take foul on Duren (DET).
Livers (DET) turns and steps into Barnes' (TOR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt. The illegal body contact occurs prior to dislodging the ball.
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Ivey (DET).
Ivey (DET) briefly places his hand to Schroder's (TOR) front and immediately slides his hand off during his drive to the basket.

After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the foul occurred prior to the inbound pass being released. Barnes (TOR) grabs and holds Bogdanovic's (DET) body off ball and the contact affects his FOM.
Siakam (TOR) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Ivey (DET), which affects Ivey's ability to gather the entry pass.
Livers (DET) turns and initiates contact to Schroder's (TOR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Trent Jr. (TOR) initiates contact with Ivey's (DET) arm that affects his ability to gather the inbound pass.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Bogdanovic (DET).
Trent Jr. (TOR) initiates some contact with Bogdanovic's (DET) arm that does not affect his ability to gather the pass.
